<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written Evidence from the Housing Ombudsman [PHS0034]</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Written Evidence from the Housing Ombudsman [PHS0034]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">am grateful to you for giving me the opportunity to contribute to your committee's </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">inquiries into complaints handling.</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 7.2pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Before addressing the specific questions posed in your letter, I think it would be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">helpful to the work of your committee if I sketched ou</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">t some background information </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">on the Housing Ombudsman.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:200%; margin:12.6pt 169.2pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt; text-decoration:underline">Background to the Housing Ombudsman Service </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Jurisdiction:</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">The statutory Housing Ombudsman was created by the Housing Act 1996 and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">commenced operating as such on 1 April 1997. The relevant provisions of the1996 Act were amended in the Housing and Regeneration Act of 2008 and, more </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">significantly, in the Localism Act of 2011. The Housing Ombudsman is a corporation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">sole and operates unde</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">r a Scheme approved by the Secretary of State (of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">DCLG).</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">am the second statutory Housing Ombudsman and was appointed in 2001. Until 1 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">April 2013 my jurisdiction covered private not-for-profit (or 'not-for-dividend') </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">landlords who are required by the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">1996 Act to be members of my Scheme "for all his </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">housing activities" and private for-profit landlords and managing agents who may </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">chose to be members. Since 1 April 2013 all the retained stock owned or managed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">by Local Housing Authorities (LHAs) or by Arms</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> Length Management Organisations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">(ALMOs) on their behalf has come within my jurisdiction. Leaseholders of all </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">member landlords are protected by my Scheme; there are, for example, about </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">300,000 leaseholders of LHAs and they, like leaseholders in the 'housin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">g </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">association' sector, do not fall into the definition of 'social housing' in the 2008 Act.</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 10.8pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Since 1 April 2013, therefore, it would be possible to categorise the Housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Ombudsman Service as a 'hybrid', having jurisdiction in both the private and public</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">sectors. This is captured in our mission statement which is "impartial dispute </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">resolution in rented housing".</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">There are now 5.1 million units and about 12.5 million people in my jurisdiction. My Service is funded by the private, for-profit and not-for-profit, landlords who pay £1.47 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">per unit per annum and grant-in-aid from government of £847,000 for the LHA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">dimens</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">ion of my jurisdiction.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Localism act 2011:</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">The Secretary of State chose my Service to be the single housing ombudsman in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Localism Act so that there would be a "common route of redress for housing tenants" and "consistency in the treatment of complaints</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">".</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 28.8pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">In 2011, the impact assessment which preceded the Bill stated that government policy was to:</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 10.8pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">"...provide a common route of redress for all complaints about the performance of social housing landlords by designating a single, specialist </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">ombudsman for soc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">ial housing. In April 2010 a new cross-domain regulatory system was brought into effect, ensuring that tenants of local authorities and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">housing associations can expect a broadly similar level of service from their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">landlord. Given the move </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">to consistent standards across social housing, we </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">now wish to put complaint handling on a more consistent footing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">designating</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> a single ombudsman for all complaints about social housing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">landlords. At the same time, we want to ensure that there continues </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">to be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">high</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> quality ombudsman service for all social housing tenants and their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">representatives"</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 7.2pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Designating my Service as the single housing ombudsman was the preferred option because of our "existing single focus on housing". The option of giving the ext</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">ended </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">jurisdiction to the Local Government Ombudsmen was rejected as that would not </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">have resulted in there being a single ombudsman "specialising" in complaints about </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">landlords as their remit covers all Local Government services. This was consistent </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">with g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">overnment's intention to have a single ombudsman in the context of a single, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">cross-domain regulator where there were "common standards set by a single regulator" and where it would make little sense for complaints about landlord performance (including agai</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">nst the standards) to be considered by two different ombudsmen.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">These changes in the Localism Act stemmed from the government's recent review of social housing regulation which concluded, among other things, that the system for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">managing social housing comp</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">laints should be changed in order to strengthen the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">role of locally elected representatives and tenant groups, and address a perceived democratic deficit in understanding of housing issues at the local level. The review </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">recommended that a 'democratic filter' should be introduced so that in future tenants </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">who had exhausted their landlord's complaints procedure would have to go through their local tenant panel, MP, or councillor, who, in turn, would seek to resolve the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">comp</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">laint before, if needed, referring the issue to the Ombudsman.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">If there had not been changes to the Bill as it passed through the House of Lords </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">complaints would only have reached me if one of these 'designated persons' had referred it on to me. If they had not, the grievance would have died where it stood </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">and complainants would have been barred from bringing the issue to me. Their only, and remote</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">, opportunity for redress would have been through the ballot box.</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 36pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Changes in the Lords resulted in residents being given a much wider range of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">choices in terms of seeking resolution of their grievances if not satisfied at the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">conclusion of their landlords'</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> internal complaints procedures (ICPs).</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Direct access to the Housing Ombudsman:</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 7.2pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">In spite of clear provision to the contrary in the Localism Act, a myth has grown up </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">that disputes cannot come to me until eight weeks have passed after completion of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">providers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">' internal complaints procedures (ICPs). This is a misunderstanding of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Act and of my Scheme approved by the Secretary of State.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">It is true that one choice would be to wait eight weeks and come straight to me but </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">residents </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">might decide instead to go to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">a designated person (any MP, a local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">councillor, or a designated tenant panel) and ask them to resolve the dispute. What is less commonly understood is that they may go to a designated person and ask </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">them to refer their dispute to me immediately. The desig</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">nated person may agree to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">or reject the request but, provided that agreement or rejection is in writing or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">confirmed in writing, the matter could be with me the same day.</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 14.4pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">This means that all tenants of councils and of private, not-for-profit landlords may </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">use the designated persons to achieve not only the 'dual track' access to me that was recommended by the Law Commission but also resolution of disputes by designated persons themselves. The choice lies with tenants depending on their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">needs and the outcomes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> they are seeking. Their landlords are best placed to help them make the right choice.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 21.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Tenants of those for-profit landlords who have chosen to join my Scheme can still </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">bring their disputes to me without having to decide whether or not to engage with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">desig</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">nated persons.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 7.2pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">The crucial upshot of these provisions is, of course, that all residents and tenants in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">my jurisdiction may have immediate and direct access to my Service if they so wish.</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Local dispute resolution:</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">We have made changes to ensure that more resources are devoted to early, local resolution where that is appropriate and proportionate. One example of this is that I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">now have the power, at any time, to promote local resolution of a dispute between </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">any landl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">ord and any tenant in my jurisdiction by either referring the complaint back to the complainant and provider (and/or a designated person) or by providing them </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">with assistance to resolve the dispute. Also, I may decide to suspend or not to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">progress an inves</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">tigation if I think there is opportunity to resolve the dispute locally. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">So, for instance, if a complainant refers a matter to me before completing an ICP, my</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">new power enables me to offer a solution to the parties there and then. Equa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">lly, I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">may propose a form of local resolution in any of the circumstances described above.</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Strategy reviews:</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 7.2pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">In 2006 we carried out a fundamental review of our core process and people development practices. In consequence, performance against targets for the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">organisation improved yearly. The work that was then required to prepare for my </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">extended jurisdiction amou</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">nted to the most far-reaching review of the Service since </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">it came into being on 1 April 1997.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">In order to support Parliament's intention that, where possible, complaints should be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">dealt with simply and quickly at local level and that an effective service i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">s provided to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">those cases which are escalated to me we executed an ambitious change </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">programme which linked into our strategic imperatives. We carried out a fundamental </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">review of all aspects of the organisation with one of our most important priorities </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">bein</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">g to re-align resources to focus on front-end delivery.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 21.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Our strategic aims for 2012-13 were delivered by means of a Transition Plan that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">identified and mapped specific, timed objectives and work-streams that:</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Clarified and defined the precise nature and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">extent of my new role;</span></p><p style="margin:1.8pt 21.6pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Developed new policy regarding management processes and learning and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">knowledge-management in the context of my new jurisdiction;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 7.2pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Reviewed governance to ensure appropriateness for a statutory ombudsman </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">and his extended role and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">jurisdiction;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Reviewed and amended the approved Scheme;</span></p><p style="margin:1.8pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Re-engineered the core dispute resolution process;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 21.6pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Designed dispute resolution principles to be supported by learning delivery </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">media.</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 36pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">In order to ensure that the internal structure of the organisation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> would be fit for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">purpose we:</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Deployed the right people in the right roles;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 28.8pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Reduced the size and cost of the leadership team so that more resources </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">were applied to front-end service delivery;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Re-configured our office space to ensure that it was suitable for the necessary </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">expansion of the team;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 7.2pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Developed internal systems to run the Designated Tenant Panels Register (in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">accordance with a specific provision in the Localism Act);</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Developed a new we</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">bsite to meet the needs of all of our key stakeholders;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 14.4pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Applied our stakeholder management and communication strategy and plan </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">as critical factors in the delivery of the overall strategy and the mitigation of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">risks.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Housing Ombudsman's</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> new role:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:113%; margin:7.2pt 14.4pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">My new, two-pronged, role is now stated succinctly in the introduction to my new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Scheme that was approved by the Secretary of State in February 2013; it is to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">resolve disputes involving members of the Scheme, including making awards of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">compensat</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">ion or other remedies when appropriate, as well as to support effective </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">landlord-tenant dispute resolution by others. This new, composite role is now </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">reflected in the changes to our strategic outcomes, revisions to the Scheme which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">regulates the Service, t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">he re-engineered core process, new Dispute Resolution </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Principles, new learning media, and a re-focussed stakeholder management </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">strategy.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:114%; margin:10.8pt 3.6pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">The first 'prong' of my role is clearly reflected in our mission statement (above). We </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">aim to provide an escalated comp</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">laint-handling and dispute-resolution service which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">is trusted, valued, and respected because it is fair, independent, impartial (free of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">bias and prejudice), effective, efficient, transparent, appropriate, proportionate, and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">relevant. Equally, we aim to p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">rovide or assist dispute resolution, especially locally, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">wherever possible and this theme is picked up in our vision which is to "work with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">others to increase trust in dispute resolution and to improve landlord and tenant </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">relations".</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 0pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">The primary outcomes o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">f our vision and mission are that, in 2016:</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 0pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Tenants and landlords have increased trust in dispute resolution;</span></p><p style="margin:1.8pt 0pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Tenant and landlord relations are improved;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Landlords have a positive view of complaints;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Designated persons are playing their part in resolving </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">disputes fairly.</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 0pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Philosophy:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:114%; margin:10.8pt 7.2pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">The changes to my jurisdiction and role as from April 2013 required a consequential </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">revision to our philosophy which is now as follows:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:114%; margin:9pt 7.2pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">"In essence, we provide a high quality, impartial service to people who live in, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">supply, or manage housing. We offer our experience, skills, expertise, and guidance to help tenants, landlords, MPs, councillors, and tenant panels. We</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:114%; margin:0pt 32.4pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">are not regulators. We are conciliators and problem-solvers. We provide objective solutions at the earli</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">est appropriate point. We make a positive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">contribution to the quality of housing and dispute resolution within the Ombudsman's jurisdiction by:</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">a) enabling and encouraging landlords to improve their standards of housing</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">management through our independent, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">impartial, and objective role by:</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 14.4pt 0pt 64.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-7.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">- explaining the advantages of complying with our determinations, and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">- encouraging a positive attitude to the value of the outcomes of complaints and similar feedback</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 10.8pt 0pt 64.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:-0.75pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">helping to improve tenants' individual and shared amenity, environment, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">and quality of life</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 39.6pt 0pt 64.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:-0.75pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">sharing our expertise, principles, and lessons learnt by highlighting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">instances of good practice revealed by our process, and</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:-0.75pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">supporting good landlord and tenant re</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">lations."</span></p><p style="margin:25.2pt 0pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Overall strategic intent:</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 25.2pt 0pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">By achieving our mission, vision, their primary outcomes, and our philosophy we </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">shall realise our overall strategic intent which is to be relevant, make an impact, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">make a difference, and add value by:</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 0pt 0pt 43.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-39.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.65pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Being a catalyst for change in the rented-housing sector having fundamentally </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">re-engineered, once again, our dispute resolution process with particular </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">emphasis on the customer's perspective;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 50.4pt 0pt 43.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-39.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.65pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Being the champion of good practice and the source of excellence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">complaint handling and dispute resolution in rented housing through </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">appropriate and proportionate methods of dissemination;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 10.8pt 0pt 43.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-39.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.65pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Demonstrating that we are making an impact by collecting more data that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">provide evidence of the success of the measures we shall</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> set for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">organisational performance, service delivery, and monitoring improvement in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">dispute resolution practice in the sector;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 39.6pt 0pt 43.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-39.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.65pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Applying our resources proportionately to the ombudsman functions of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">investigation, systemic failures, and knowledge disseminati</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">on.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 7.2pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Developing, improving, and enhancing the following nine characteristics of the value </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">added by our service delivery will make a significant contribution to the success of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">our strategy:</span></p><p style="margin:14.4pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">i)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">We help improve customer service and positive relationships:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:10.8pt 10.8pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">The outputs of our investigations where service failure or maladministration is found </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">are in the form of recommendations or orders, or both. They may require providers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">to:</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Tell us how they propose to put right the failings we have identified;</span></p><p style="margin:3.6pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Give, or rest</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">ore to, residents their entitlements under statute or contract;</span></p><p style="margin:1.8pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Introduce, amend, or properly apply their policies;</span></p><p style="margin:3.6pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Make an apology;</span></p><p style="margin:1.8pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Pay compensation.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:10.8pt 10.8pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Whether or not we find maladministration our principal aims in composing decisions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">are to:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:113%; margin:10.8pt 43.2pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Put residents into the position in which they should have been but for their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">provider's failure;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:113%; margin:0pt 54pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Enable providers to learn from our findings and apply that learning to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">improvement of the quality of the service they provide;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 7.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Help </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">improve or sustain a positive relationship between providers and residents;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 7.2pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Contribute to the improvement of customer service.</span></p><p style="margin:18pt 0pt 0pt 10.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">ii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Providers comply with our recommendations and orders:</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 3.6pt 0pt 7.2pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">There have been very few instances since 1997 in which providers have faile</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">d to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">comply with my recommendations or orders. They recognise, as the Law </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Commission put it (in their Consultation Paper 196 ) the "political or moral pressure" </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">on them to put things right following a decision of the Ombudsman. They are also confident that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> the Ombudsman is independent and operates an impartial, quality-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">managed process that draws conclusions only from careful analysis of available evidence.</span></p><p style="margin:12.6pt 0pt 0pt 10.8pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11.5pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">iii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">We provide advice, assistance, and signposting:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:112%; margin:10.8pt 0pt 0pt 7.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Even before 1 April 2013 and the re-configuration of our core process to concentrate </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">resources on early dispute resolution, about 90% of cases were already being closed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">without investigation.</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0.25pt"><tr style="height:28.55pt"><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; vertical-align:top; width:73.2pt"><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Year</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; vertical-align:top; width:116.9pt"><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Total complaints closed</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; vertical-align:top; width:119.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-s