 complaints which in his opinion could still be pursued through providers' procedures.</span></p><p style="margin:9pt 3.6pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Unde</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">r the new Scheme the value that we can add in these circumstances is even </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">greater because I now have the power, at any time, to promote local resolution of a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">dispute by either referring the complaint back to the complainant and provider and/or a designated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt"> person; or providing assistance to the complainant and provider and /or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">a designated person to resolve the dispute.</span></p><p style="margin:10.8pt 10.8pt 7.2pt 3.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Many other cases are outside jurisdiction (OSJ) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">(e.g. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">the provider may not be a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">member of the Scheme, or the issue may not relate to a land</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">lord and tenant </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">relationship </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:0.05pt">etc) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">and we may not be able to assist further. Nevertheless, whenever </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">we can, we give information or advice on process and, where possible, signpost people to other agencies that may be able to help them. The table below </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">demons</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">trates this activity up to the commencement of my new jurisdiction and our </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">new processes and procedures.</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt"><tr style="height:16.55pt"><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; vertical-align:middle; width:113.4pt"><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">Gateway Outcomes</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; vertical-align:middle; width:85.05pt"><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.05pt">2008-09</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:sol